GRAPH EXPLORER FRONTEND ROADMAP (PHASED, HIGH ROI -> LOW ROI)
Audience: implementation agents. Style: step-by-step, minimal ambiguity.
Goal: make graph feel premium: clarity, trust (evidence), speed, workflow.

GLOBAL PRINCIPLES (apply everywhere)
- Canvas is sacred: details should be peekable/temporary unless pinned.
- One action = one obvious result. No "mystery state".
- Evidence-first UI: edges carry trust. Nodes carry identity.
- Prefer progressive enhancement: ship scaffolds early, deepen later.
- Avoid global relayout on every merge; favor local updates.

DATA / UI TERMINOLOGY
- Selection: none | node | edge | multi
- Inspector: right-side sheet/drawer for selection details + actions
- Lens: curated multi-step /graph/query expansion
- Typed expand: per-node-type expansion button (edgeTypes + direction + limit + sort)
- BFS expand: /graph/subgraph "Expand all neighbors"

                                                                                                                     frontend merge logic would be:
  on expansion response:
    for each node in response.data.nodes:
      if node key NOT in canvas → add node
      if node key already in canvas → skip (already rendered)

    for each edge in response.data.edges:
      add edge (connects to existing or new nodes)

