Not done (from EXPLORER_STATE.md):

- [ ] EdgeInstance + RelationshipGroup model
  Currently: flat edge map (one edge per key). Multiple edges between the same pair overwrite each other.
  Why: The backend can return multiple edge types between the same two nodes (e.g. Gene–Disease connected
  by ASSOCIATED_WITH_DISEASE + CURATED_FOR + CAUSES). RelationshipGroups let us render one visual edge
  on the canvas while the inspector shows all underlying evidence edges stacked. Without this, users
  either see duplicate overlapping edges or lose evidence.

- [ ] Provenance tracking (ProvenanceEvent)
  Currently: nodes/edges have no record of how they entered the graph.
  Why: After several expansions + lens switches, users ask "how did this node get here?" Provenance
  answers that — "Added by: Clinical lens → step 1" or "Expanded from BRCA1 → Find Diseases".
  Also enables the "Why am I seeing this?" UI in Phase 2.3, and deduplicating repeated fetches.

- [ ] Hard invariants enforced in merge
  Currently: reducer merges nodes/edges but doesn't enforce "no edge without both endpoints" or
  "selection points to something that exists".
  Why: Without invariants, removing a node can leave orphan edges in state, or selection can reference
  a deleted node — causing UI to show stale data or crash. Invariants eliminate an entire class of bugs.

- [ ] Action log / event sourcing
  Currently: actions fire-and-forget with no history.
  Why: Required for undo/redo (Phase 4.2), shareable session links (Phase 7.3), and replay debugging.
  Every action (expand, filter, remove, lens switch) gets appended to a log that can be replayed.

- [ ] Lens compiler (seed-type-agnostic)
  Currently: lenses are hardcoded step arrays assuming Gene seed.
  Why: The explorer should work from any entity page (Drug, Disease, Variant). The same "Clinical" lens
  should compile different query steps depending on seed type. Without this, adding the explorer to
  the Drug page requires duplicating all lens definitions.

- [ ] Evidence overlay / relationship enrichment
  Currently: fetching more data always adds new nodes to the canvas.
  Why: Users often want deeper evidence between two already-visible nodes (e.g. "what else connects
  BRCA1 to Breast Cancer?") without cluttering the graph with new nodes. Enrichment fetches additional
  edge types between an existing pair and stacks them into the RelationshipGroup.

- [ ] ExplorerSession: entry from any entity page
  Currently: explorer is Gene-page-only with a single seed.
  Why: Drug, Disease, and Variant pages should each launch the explorer with their own seed type.
  Multi-seed workflows (compare two diseases, intersect drug targets) require seeds as NodeRef[],
  not a single gene ID.

- [ ] Schema-driven dynamic expansions
  Currently: expansion options are hardcoded per entity type in NODE_EXPANSION_CONFIG.
  Why: As new edge types are added to the backend, the frontend must be manually updated. Schema-driven
  expansions auto-generate "Expand..." actions from /graph/schema, keeping curated ones pinned at top
  and new ones under "More". Future-proofs the explorer against schema changes.

- [ ] Evidence weight/quality badges
  Currently: edges show raw field values (numSources, numExperiments) with no interpretation.
  Why: Users need at-a-glance trust signals. Badges like "Curated", "High confidence", "ClinVar reviewed"
  are computed from edge instance fields and shown on edges/nodes in the inspector and tooltips.
  This is the "evidence-first UI" principle in action.

